      "content": "Research consistently shows that high-density networks increase \"eyes on the street,\" which strengthens social control and interaction, but it is rarely cited as the single most effective method for building cohesion. Sociologists like Jane Jacobs and Stephen Kellert emphasize density as a primary catalyst for sidewalk vitality, though the actual success of social outcomes depends heavily on intentional landscape architecture and community design. For a council presentation, citing these nuances alongside implementation studies will provide a robust and realistic argument.",
